post_text: Great Idea!
shared_text:
Julie New Harbaugh
August 12, 2019 at 12:14 PM ¬∑

PSA for all soon-to-be kindergarten mamas...
Practice eating ‚Äúschool lunch‚Äù with your kiddo. Make sure they can open everything you send with them. Talk about not eating off of the table in the lunchroom!!! Set a timer for 15 minutes and talk about how they may not finish eating and that‚Äôs ok. (This was HARD for little man.) Practice packing everything back up and talk about what is trash and what should come back home in their lunch box. Kindergarten lunch is a big adjustment and your child‚Äôs teacher will be super appreciative if you have prepared them for the experience!

post_text:
Dickson County Schools 2020 Summer Meal Service Plan
Summer Feeding
Dickson County Schools are proud to be able to serve meals to students during the Summer of 2020. Meals are provided free to children ages 0-18. Families do not need to provide proof of school enrollment, income, or free/reduced lunch eligibility. Children must be present to receive the meal. A breakfast and lunch will be pre-packaged and distributed to families. Meals will be distributed in a ‚Äògrab and go‚Äô, so there is no need for a family to leave their vehicle. There will be no access to school buildings available during this time.

When: May 27th through June 30th
Where:
- Creek Wood High School: Main bus loop - gym entrance 12-noon
- Dickson Middle: Auditorium entrance (Frosty Jug side) 10 ‚Äì noon
- Bruce Perry Homes: Brittney the Lunch Bus 10 am ‚Äì 10:30 am
- Crosby Terrace: Brittney the Lunch Bus 10:45 am ‚Äì 11:15 am
- Dickson Housing: Brittney the Lunch Bus 11:30 am ‚Äì Noon

shared_text:
Learning through movement
April 23 at 7:51 AM ¬∑

Laterality

Toddlers use both hands and feet equally. Becoming aware that you have a left and right develops during kindergarten.

To make automatic movements you develop a preference side with your hands, feet, eyes, ears and brain. Both sides will also learn to work together.

You not only have left and right side but also a bottom / top and front / back. Babies start with this skill by crawling. Laterality is the pioneer in developing sense of direction.

‚úÖPlay like in this video is really important.

For complex skills, such as maths, reading and writing, this development is very important. This development is completed around 8 years old. It is an enormous challenge to start reading, writing and arithmetic as the body is not yet fully developed.
